Biological analogy

Your immune system works this way.

Millions of immune cells exist briefly.

They perform a task.

Most disappear.

Memory cells preserve what matters.

Pantheon already has an analogue:

Mother Duck.

The temporary workers don’t need permanence.

Mother Duck remembers the lessons.

