Pseudo-Expendable

I like this wording because it captures an important distinction.

The worker is disposable.

The work is not.

Even better:

The worker isn’t really “dying.”

Its experience is harvested before retirement.

That mirrors your earlier Möbius idea.

Spawn
↓
Perform mission
↓
Report
↓
Knowledge integrated
↓
Retire
↓
Spawn improved successor

Nothing valuable is lost.

Only the temporary container disappears.

